pr_review_body:
@SamuelGabriel Thanks a lot for the contribution. 

We did some checks on our end as well and we think that this is a good addition, especially for people who work on similar but different datasets than ImageNet. I should also note that your contribution and proposed approach helped us review the API of the augmentation code, so your contribution here is much bigger than just adding the TrivialAugment. Thank you!

As this PR contains also bug fixes for RandAugment, I'll merge this to get things going and we can follow up any further improvements on separate PRs. I just have one question for you below, please let me know.

@bnmajor thanks for testing! Nothing? Even if the `* 2` is removed?

Overall, an improvement nonetheless.

Could the limit please checked and excluded for the JupyterLite case if  `cpu_count` is not correctly reported?

Can we update this from usage_lib.py? I think we can do this way;

1. Generate a method that gets all internal config from `GetInternalConfigRequest`. 
2. When the dashboard first starts, we get internal config and update only relevant fields only once (in this case memory monitor config)

A few considerations on this,

We haven't be using refactor a lot, although in this case it makes sense, but since this makes sense, let's make this a patch, otherwise it will not have impact.

so in the `.releaserc.json` file, change this to:
```json
{
  "plugins": [
    ["@semantic-release/commit-analyzer", {
      "preset": "angular",
      "releaseRules": [
        {"type": "chore", "release": "patch"},
        {"type": "refactor", "release": "patch"}
      ]
    }],
    "@semantic-release/release-notes-generator",
    "@semantic-release/github"
  ]
}
```

otherwise this will not produce a release.

In another topic, i would suggest to instead of move the code into the `pandas_profiling` repo, we could fork the `missingno` project and upload this to pypi under our name or pupose them to change this somehow.

But this is just my two cents for this

@vfdev-5 I might not be the best person to "review" this PR but I can confirm that any modification done on your side looks great. It was a good idea to do most of the work needed on `fill` on separate PRs. I had a look also at your PRs #6595 and #6599 and the direction looks great. Maintaining `F` JIT-scriptable is a major win, thanks a lot for your work on making it possible. Thank you for the excellent work.

@pmeier Could you please give us an independent review on this PR?

FYI: follow up work we should do is ensuring the signatures of `F` and `_Feature` are aligned. After merging this PR, the signatures of the dispatchers on the base class don't match (one uses Sequences and the other uses List).
